post_text: FUN, FUN, FUN! The Gadsden ISD encourages families to make the learning-at-home experience as enjoyable as possible. In support of this endeavor, Friday, May 8 will be the first of the Family Fun Fridays for the remainder of the school year. GISD encourages our students and their families to engage in fun family experiences outside of learning. No lessons, no phone calls from teachers and no Google Classrooms. This is your time to relax, unwind and engage in family living. School district offices and campuses will be closed on Friday, but open during regular operating hours, Monday through Thursday. Wi-Fi Hotspots have increased in number. Along with the high school hotspots, all elementary schools now have Wi-Fi access in their parking lots. Teacher Appreciation Week is this week, May 3 through May 7, show how much you value your teachers, and their efforts during these unusual times. Let them know you recognize with gratitude their efforts this year.

COVID-19 testing will be conducted at the Chaparral Local Public Health Office every Thursday:

Chaparral Public Health Office- 317 McCombs, Chaparral, NM. Testing will be conducted every Thursday, 8:30a.m. to 11:30a.m. The first testing session will be held on Thursday, April 2nd at the Chaparral Public Health Office.

This is going into effect immediately and can be done by medical provider referral ONLY, meaning the PCPâ€™s office or personal from the ERD will need to contact the DOH at 575-824-3454 (ext 100) to schedule an appt. for their patient. When making the referral, you may need to provide general demographic information (Patient name, DOB, etc.), those scheduling at DOH will be able to provide you more information/direction on this. Patients who do not have a primary care provider can contact the Coronavirus Hotline at 1-855-600-3453 to be screened for a referral.

GISD ACTIONS FOLLOWING GOVERNOR'S ANNOUNCEMENT ON COVID-19:

In light of the Governor's press conference on the COVID-19, Gadsden ISD will be temporarily suspending all out of state travel. Any travel to El Paso will be considered local therefore will be allowed at this point.

GISD will continue to monitor the updates on the COVID- 19 virus in New Mexico and follow preventative directions from the State, GISD Nursing Department, and health agencies in our area. We continue to advise our students and parents that prevention measures outlined by health agencies be followed especially washing hands at every opportunity, establishing safe space between persons and being aware that if a student exhibits any type of flu related symptoms to seek the advise of health professionals and not attend school.
text:
GISD ACTIONS FOLLOWING GOVERNOR'S ANNOUNCEMENT ON COVID-19:

In light of the Governor's press conference on the COVID-19, Gadsden ISD will be temporarily suspending all out of state travel. Any travel to El Paso will be considered local therefore will be allowed at this point.

GISD will continue to monitor the updates on the COVID- 19 virus in New Mexico and follow preventative directions from the State, GISD Nursing Department, and health agencies in our area. We continue to advise our students and parents that prevention measures outlined by health agencies be followed especially washing hands at every opportunity, establishing safe space between persons and being aware that if a student exhibits any type of flu related symptoms to seek the advise of health professionals and not attend school.

Adalberto "Beto" Romero IV was a sophomore and baseball player at Gadsden High School with a promising athletic and academic future ahead of him He was a student with a 4.2 GPA with many dreams ahead of him.

Unfortunately, on April 3, 2019 his life was cut short killed in a hit and run accident near his home. In honor of Beto, Gadsden ISD is joining with Gadsden High school to sponsor a 3K Walk-A-Thon to establish a scholarship fund in his name for Gadsden High baseball player.

GISD and Gadsden High is seeking donations in order to hold a Walk-A-Thon in honor of Beto which will be on Saturday, April 4, 2020 at Gadsden High School. Registration forms will be available at Gadsden HS front office. All proceeds collected will go towards a scholarship for a GHS senior baseball player.

For more information, donors can contact: Dennice: (915) 922-8116, Beto: (575) 386-3902, Liza: (915) 497-1453 or Lorraine: (575) 373-5516.

Contributions can be made to the following account that has been establish at Bank of the West, 300 N. Anthony Dr.Anthony, NM 88021, at Acct # 062112503.

post_text:
Celebrating Authentic Family Engagement Practices at Gadsden ISD!

The entire campus at Santa Teresa Middle School read the heartwarming story, "Too Many Tamales" by Gary Soto. As the story reads, students participated in making sweet tamales to enter a contest with parents. Making tamales is a tradition in Latin cultures during special occasions and involves preparing the corn dough, cooking and preparing the filling, soaking the corn husks, then spreading, filling and wrapping. Parents took the tamales home to cook then brought them back to enter the contest which was scored on originality, flavor, and presentation.

The educational experience was integrated into all the classrooms. Students learned the literary elements of the story, the cultural aspects, math strategies to convert tamales into dozens and measure the ingredients needed. They also learned about converting Fahrenheit to Celsius for cooking the tamales.

Family Engagement is one of the best strategies for student success - Ms. Rosa Lovelace, Principal for Santa Teresa Elementary
